{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-jsx","path":"/posts/2015-06-30-transistor","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"7466e009-9f5e-55fb-ae21-1177fd7f032d","html":"<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 700px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/78c49159ff71255a7f2dd8a1980bc290/6a068/transistor.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 55.42857142857143%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Transistor\"\n        title=\"Transistor\"\n        src=\"/static/78c49159ff71255a7f2dd8a1980bc290/29d31/transistor.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/78c49159ff71255a7f2dd8a1980bc290/e52aa/transistor.jpg 175w,\n/static/78c49159ff71255a7f2dd8a1980bc290/70ebb/transistor.jpg 350w,\n/static/78c49159ff71255a7f2dd8a1980bc290/29d31/transistor.jpg 700w,\n/static/78c49159ff71255a7f2dd8a1980bc290/6a068/transistor.jpg 960w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.supergiantgames.com/games/transistor/\">Transistor</a>. I am speechless. In fact, it left me crying by the end credits.</p>\n<p>What a perfectly crafted game: the art, the gameplay, and—woah—the storytelling. Every aspect was perfect, each given its own unique treatment. Yet, they were all tied together by a dominant theme so strong the whole thing seemed almost more of an “experience” than a “game”. The ending was so powerful it leaves you with that lingering feeling you get after reading a good novel. Transistor was one of the best gaming experience I’ve ever had. It will surely stick with me for a while.</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Transistor","date":"June 30, 2015"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/posts/2015-06-30-transistor","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/posts/2014-06-08-webgl-gpu-particles","type":"post"},"frontmatter":{"title":"WebGL GPU Particles"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/posts/2016-07-16-why-im-not-playing-pokmon-go","type":"post"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Why I'm Not Playing Pokémon Go"}}}},"staticQueryHashes":[]}